In a small #pot, bring ¾ cup salted water (1½ cups for 4 servings) to a boil. Stir in @white quinoa{1/2%cup} and @veggie stock concentrate{1}; cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until quinoa is tender and liquid has absorbed, ~{15-20%minutes}. Transfer to a large #bowl and let cool for at least ~{5%minutes} (you'll finish the quinoa in Step 5).

While quinoa cooks, wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens; mince whites. Dice @tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces.

Pat @organic chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with half the @Mexican spice blend{1%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings), a big pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> Swap in chicken or organic chicken for pork; cook until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

== Lime Crema ==

While pork cooks, in a small #bowl, combine @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, half the lime zest, and @salt{}. Add @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

In a separate small #bowl, combine cilantro, scallion whites, 1 tsp @olive oil{4%teaspoon}, juice from one lime wedge, and as much remaining lime zest as you like. Season generously with salt and pepper. Taste and add more lime juice if desired.

== Tomato Quinoa Salad ==

Stir tomato, scallion greens, @pepitas{1/2%ounce}, 1 TBSP olive oil, juice from two lime wedges, and a pinch of salt and pepper into bowl with quinoa.

== To Serve ==

Slice pork crosswise.

> Slice chicken or organic chicken crosswise. Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Divide pork and tomato quinoa salad between plates. Drizzle pork with lime crema and cilantro sauce. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.